      "end": 18.0,
      "text": "D-U-N-K-E-L-B-E-R-G.com.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 19.58,
      "end": 20.5,
      "text": "Asop's fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 21.04,
      "end": 22.42,
      "text": "The Eagle and the Arrow.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 23.82,
      "end": 28.54,
      "text": "An Eagle set perched on a lofty rock, keeping a sharp lookout for prey.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 29.54,
      "end": 34.62,
      "text": "A Huntsman concealed in a cleft of the mountain and on the watch for game,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 35.0,
      "end": 38.02,
      "text": "spied him there, and shot an arrow at him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 38.48,
      "end": 42.58,
      "text": "The shaft struck him full in the breast and pierced him through and through.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 44.02,
      "end": 50.48,
      "text": "As he lay in the agonies of death, he turned his eyes upon the arrow.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 51.58,
      "end": 60.62,
      "text": "A cruel fate, he cried, that I should perish thus, but O, fate more cruel still,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 61.32,
      "end": 68.44,
      "text": "that the arrow which kills me should be winged with an Eagle's feathers.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 69.96,
      "end": 72.76,
      "text": "End of the Eagle and the Arrow.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
